WARNINGS AND NON-FINAL ATTEMPTS
-------------------------------
1. The repository's pre-existing build/ cache names a different source path.
   It was not modified; the clean /tmp build above was used.
2. A first attempt to launch the final production executable without sourcing
   Geant4 failed before initialization with missing libG4zlib.so and exit 127.
   No events were run. The successful command above used the stated environment.
3. Geant4 warns that the pre-existing zero-density Ar_gas is assigned its
   minimum density 1e-25 g/cm3. The Ar fraction is zero and the configured
   detector gas remains He/CF4 60/40 at 1 atm.
4. The startup physics dump precedes macro execution, so it prints the default
   electron StepFunction=(0.2,0.01 mm). The unchanged macro applies
   0.001 0.01 mm and Geant4 invokes /run/physicsModified before events.
5. The retained run summary labels the gun as geantino, reports infinite
   geantino activity, and prints an invalid visible-energy minimum. The
   application replaces the gun particle with Sr-90 during generation and the
   visible-energy accumulator is disabled; none of those fields is used here.
6. thisroot.sh emitted a shell-specific null-byte/root-config warning in one
   diagnostic invocation. Direct ROOTSYS/PATH/LD_LIBRARY_PATH exports, shown
   above, were used for the final build, tests, and analysis.
7. A preliminary full run completed before the recorder was tightened to
   suppress rare non-beta RadioactiveDecay electrons at write time. Its
   downstream direct-beta CSV and PNG were byte-identical to the final run.
   The final run documented here supersedes it and has exactly 6000000 raw rows.

SELECTION LIMITATION
--------------------
The retained simulation analysis contains no selection beyond its exact
FullyContained cut followed by requiring an available reconstructed direction.
Selected is therefore FullyContained&&RecoAvailable. No additional selection
was inferred; any further event selection cannot be reproduced from this
repository.

